            "If MgSO4 contraindicated or ineffective: Diazepam 10 mg IV slow",
            "Treat hypertension: IV Hydralazine 5 mg bolus or IV Labetalol 20 mg then 40 mg if no response at 10 min",
            "Target BP: 140-155/90-105 mmHg — avoid sudden drops",
            "Deliver fetus — definitive treatment is delivery",
            "Plan for induction or caesarean section once stabilised",
            "Monitor: BP Q15min, SpO2, respiratory rate (MgSO4 toxicity), urine output, DTRs hourly",
            "Monitor fetal heart rate continuously"
          ],
          "counselling": "Explain eclampsia and need for delivery. MgSO4 essential to prevent further seizures."
        },
        {
          "severity": "post_ictal",
          "criteria": "Seizure controlled, stable vital signs but still hypertensive",
          "treatment": [
            "Continue MgSO4 infusion for 24 hours after last seizure",
            "Continue antihypertensives to maintain BP <155/105",
            "Monitor for recurrent seizures, pulmonary oedema, renal function",
            "Plan delivery — timing depends on gestational age and maternal/fetal stability",
            "After delivery: continue MgSO4 for 24h postpartum, monitor for postpartum eclampsia",
            "If <34 weeks: consider steroid course for fetal lung maturity before delivery if stable"
          ]
